Subject: List of quarries served by the Ffestiniog Railway 
To: Dylan
Content:
The Festiniog Railway served a cluster of quarries around the town of Blaenau Ffestiniog. Most of these were slate quarries, although granite quarries and zinc mines were also connected by narrow gauge tramways to the railway.[1] Ffestiniog Railway Welsh Highland Railway Welsh Highland Heritage Railway Ffestiniog Railway Welsh Highland Railway Welsh Highland Heritage Railway Ffestiniog Railway Welsh Highland Railway Ffestiniog Railway Society Festiniog Railway Heritage Group Welsh Highland Railway Society Welsh Highland Railway Heritage Group Festiniog Railway Letter Service Welsh Highland Railway restoration Great Little Trains of Wales Bala Lake Railway Brecon Mountain Railway Corris Railway Fairbourne Railway Ffestiniog Railway Llanberis Lake Railway Rhyl Miniature Railway Snowdon Mountain Railway Talyllyn Railway Teifi Valley Railway Vale of Rheidol Railway Welsh Highland Railway Welsh Highland Heritage Railway Welshpool and Llanfair Light Railway Amman Valley Railway Barry Tourist Railway Garw Valley Railway Gwili Railway Llanelli and Mynydd Mawr Railway Llangollen Railway Pontypool and Blaenavon Railway Swansea Vale Railway (closed) Conwy Valley Railway Museum Narrow Gauge Railway Museum
